Check if git is installed
      git -version

Create repository

      mkdir <reponame>
      cd <reponame>
      git init
      
Add file to local repository
      touch <filename>
      git add <filename>            ( to track the files )
      
configure username
      git config -

Check status of git and current branch working on
      git status
      
See changes made to files
      git diff
      
Save the changes with a short message
      git commit -m "commit message"

Add a remote connection
      git remote add origin <URLFROMGITHUB>
      
Push work to your remote
      git push origin master
              <remote><branch> 
Pull in changes
      git pull origin master
              <remote><branch>
              
View remote address
      git remote -v

Fork from other repo using GUI on github and then clone in CLI
      git clone <URLFROMGITHUB>
      
Connect to original repository
      git remote add upstream <urlfromgithub>
      
Create a new branch
      git branch <BRANCHNAME>

Switch onto new branch
      git checkout <BRANCHNAME>      

Rename a branch currently working on
      git branch -m <NEWBRANCHNAME>

LIst all branches
      git branch
